    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i just don't know... i've read some things online saying that if you have a mild infection and the symptoms vanish, you're actually better off stopping to preserve your natural microbiome. my friend who is a nutritionist said that taking antibiotics longer than strictly necessary is actually more harmful to your long term gut health than a quick relapse would be. do you really think the risk of resistance is that high for just one person's skin infection?",
